// both stringbuilder and stringbuffer have the same methods

METHODS SAME AS STRING:

length()
charAt(index)
indexOf(str) // String allows characters, but stringbuilder and stringbuffer allows only non characters 
indexOf(str,fromIndex)
lastIndexOf(str)
LastIndexOf(str,fromIndex)
compareTo(sb) // sb is an object
substring(beginIndex)
substring(beginIndex, endIndex)
chars() gives a stream of integers

METHODS PRESENT ONLY IN STRINGBUILDER AND STRINGBUFFER:

append(x) - boolean, int, char, float, string, object
insert(offset, x) - boolean, int, char, float, string, object
setChatAt(index, c)
reverse() - inplace reversing
deletecharAt(index)
delete(start, end) -  start is inclusive, end is exclusive
capacity()
replace(start, end, str) // not replace(char1, char2)
